The paper discusses the current attack techniques used to convey PDF malware, which falls under the category of cyber-security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses state-of-the-art PDF malware analysis tools, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses limitations and open issues of the current defense mechanisms, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CY).
